            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>157</offset>
                <text>He was born after a normal&#13;
pregnancy period, full term by normal vaginal&#13;
delivery and his birth weight was 2.8 kg.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>275</offset>
                <text>Routine prenatal follow-up and ultrasounds&#13;
were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>332</offset>
                <text>There was no history of child&#13;
abuse, trauma and fever.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>388</offset>
                <text>He was only breast&#13;
fed and was having vitamin-D supplement 400&#13;
U/day.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>460</offset>
                <text>The mother and father was the first&#13;
cousin once removed.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>522</offset>
                <text>On physical examination of the patient, he was&#13;
irritable, crying when lower limbs were touched.</text>
                <annotation id="5">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0000737</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="48"/>
                    <text>irritable</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>620</offset>
                <text>All vital signs were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>649</offset>
                <text>His weight, length&#13;
and head circumference percentiles were 50-&#13;
75p, 10-25p and 10-25 p, respectively.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>753</offset>
                <text>There&#13;
was bilateral swelling and tenderness over his&#13;
shins, without any erythema or ecchymosis.</text>
                <annotation id="6">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="Comment">! Add term requested</infon>
                    <location length="8" offset="21"/>
                    <text>swelling</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="9">
