                    <node refid="11" role="source"/>
                    <node refid="9" role="target"/>
                </relation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>851</offset>
                <text>He&#13;
kept his lower limbs at flexion posture.</text>
                <annotation id="12">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0005750</infon>
                    <location length="30" offset="13"/>
                    <text>lower limbs at flexion posture</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>896</offset>
                <text>The&#13;
remaining systemic examinations were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>947</offset>
                <text>Laboratory investigations showed elevated levels&#13;
of erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR, 60&#13;
mm/hr) and alkaline phosphatase (537 IU/L),&#13;
and a mild thrombocytosis (572.000 /mm3).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1129</offset>
                <text>Peripheral blood smear showed hypo chromic&#13;
red cells, target cells and thrombocytosis with&#13;
no other abnormality.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1244</offset>
                <text>Serum C-reactive protein&#13;
(CRP), calcium, amylase, parathormone, 25-OH&#13;
vitamin-D levels and the other biochemical and&#13;
hematological evaluations were normal.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1403</offset>
                <text>Patient’s&#13;
and the mother’s serology for syphilis (VDRL)&#13;
was nonreactive.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1478</offset>
                <text>Serum immunoglobulin and&#13;
urine analyses were normal, and serology for&#13;
viral infections was negative.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>1581</offset>
                <text>Radiological&#13;
examination showed cortical thickening, sub&#13;
periosteal reaction and new bone formation&#13;
in the mandible, bilateral clavicles and long&#13;
bones (Fig. 1a and b).</text>
